# Nokia 6103 phone controller node.
#
# The phone is a Bluetooth INPUT, not a pinged LAN device (no HOST_IP -> it never
# shows on the network map; it appears in Pluto Control as an input source). This
# dir houses the phone app (midlet/) and declares the node.
#
# The RUNTIME config lives on the PI node, because the Pi hosts the Bluetooth link
# and the drive: set NOKIA_ENGINE_PORT / NOKIA_ADDR / NOKIA_CHANNEL in
# nodes/local/pi/.env (see its .env.sample).

NODE_NAME=Nokia Phone
